# .claude — flutter-monorepo
#
# Project-level instructions for Claude / AI assistants working in this repo.
# These instructions are loaded automatically when Claude opens this workspace.

## Project overview
Flutter/Dart monorepo managed with Melos.
- `apps/`      — Flutter applications
- `packages/`  — Shared Dart/Flutter packages

## Stack
- Flutter 3.x (stable channel)
- Dart 3.x
- Melos 6.x for workspace orchestration
- very_good_analysis for linting

## Key commands
```bash
melos bootstrap          # install all dependencies
melos run lint           # flutter analyze across all packages
melos run format         # dart format across all packages
melos run test           # flutter test across all packages
melos run build          # build all packages
melos run hooks:install  # register git hooks
```

## Code conventions
- Always use `declare(strict_types=1)` — wait, this is Dart. Always use explicit types.
- Follow `analysis_options.yaml` rules — `very_good_analysis` base.
- All public APIs must have dartdoc comments (`///`).
- Prefer `const` constructors wherever possible.
- Use single quotes for strings.
- Trailing commas on all multi-line structures.
- Never use `print()` — use a proper logger.

## File structure conventions
- One class per file.
- File names in `snake_case`.
- Test files mirror source: `src/foo.dart` → `test/foo_test.dart`.

## Git conventions
- Conventional Commits: `feat(scope): description`
- Never commit directly to `main` — always use a PR.
- Tag format for package releases: `<package_name>-v<semver>`

## What NOT to do
- Do not modify `pubspec.lock` manually.
- Do not add dependencies without checking `melos.yaml` first.
- Do not skip `melos bootstrap` after pulling changes.
